<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head><persName type="from">Count Wydenbruck</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward.</persName></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Oakland, Md.,</hi>
                                    </placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 30, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I received yesterday from Mexico the official news that the
                                unfortunate emperor Maximilian was shot June nineteenth, (19th,)
                                seven (7) morning.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>WYDENBRUCK.</signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>